text.section:
Except as otherwise provided by law, conveyance of property by deed instead of foreclosure under this section may not affect or impair any other lien against the property or any existing recorded or unrecorded interest in the property, including:
Future installments of special assessments;
Liens recorded by the State;
Easements or rights-of-way;
Private deed restrictions;
Security interests and mortgages; or
Tax liens of other taxing jurisdictions that do not consent to a release of their liens.

A tax lien against property held by or under the control of an authority may be released or abated at any time by one or more of the following:
A county or municipal corporation with respect to a lien held by the county or municipal corporation;
The governing body of any taxing jurisdiction other than the State, county, or municipal corporation with respect to a lien held by the taxing jurisdiction;
A public water or sewer authority with respect to a tax lien or right to collect a tax held by the public water or sewer authority; or
The State Comptroller with respect to a State tax lien.
